df_2018 = df[df["Timestamp"].dt.year == 2018]
 
df_station = df_2018[df_2018["station"] == "Lal Bahadur Shastri Nagar, Kalaburagi - KSPCB"]

def classify_season(month):
    if month in [12, 1, 2]:  
        return "Winter"
    elif month in [3, 4, 5]:  
        return "Summer"
    elif month in [6, 7, 8, 9]:  
        return "Monsoon"
    else:
        return "Other"  

df_station["Season"] = df_station["Timestamp"].dt.month.map(classify_season)

df_station = df_station[df_station["Season"] != "Other"]

seasonal_avg_pm25 = df_station.groupby("Season")["PM2.5"].mean()

highest_pollution_season = seasonal_avg_pm25.idxmax()
highest_pm25_value = seasonal_avg_pm25.max()

print("Average PM2.5 concentration per season in 2018:")
print(seasonal_avg_pm25)
print(f"\nThe season with the highest PM2.5 pollution is {highest_pollution_season} with an average PM2.5 of {highest_pm25_value:.2f}")

print("In winter, cold air traps smoke and dust near the ground, making the air more polluted.")

Average PM2.5 concentration per season in 2018:
Season
Monsoon    34.425196
Summer           NaN
Winter     67.492344
Name: PM2.5, dtype: float64

The season with the highest PM2.5 pollution is Winter with an average PM2.5 of 67.49
In winter, cold air traps smoke and dust near the ground, making the air more polluted.

df_2021 = df[df["Timestamp"].dt.year == 2021]

station_name = "Lal Bahadur Shastri Nagar, Kalaburagi - KSPCB"
df_station = df_2021[df_2021["station"] == station_name]

df_station["Weekday"] = df_station["Timestamp"].dt.weekday

df_station["Day_Type"] = df_station["Weekday"].apply(lambda x: "Weekday" if x < 5 else "Weekend")

monthly_avg_pm25 = df_station.groupby([df_station["Timestamp"].dt.month, "Day_Type"])["PM2.5"].mean().unstack()
monthly_avg_pm25["Weekday"] = monthly_avg_pm25["Weekday"].interpolate(method = "linear")
monthly_avg_pm25["Weekend"] = monthly_avg_pm25["Weekend"].interpolate(method = "linear")


plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.plot(monthly_avg_pm25.index, monthly_avg_pm25["Weekday"], marker=".", linestyle="-", label="Weekdays", color="blue")
plt.plot(monthly_avg_pm25.index, monthly_avg_pm25["Weekend"], marker="o", linestyle="--", label="Weekends", color="red")

plt.show()

df_2022 = df[df["Timestamp"].dt.year == 2022]

def classify_season(month):
    if month in [3, 4, 5]: 
        return "Summer"
    elif month in [6, 7, 8, 9]: 
        return "Monsoon"

df_2022["Season"] = df_2022["Timestamp"].dt.month.map(classify_season)


seasonal_avg_pm25 = df_2022.groupby(["state", "Season"])["PM2.5"].mean().unstack()

seasonal_avg_pm25["Percentage Change"] = abs(((seasonal_avg_pm25["Monsoon"] - seasonal_avg_pm25["Summer"]) / seasonal_avg_pm25["Summer"]) * 100)

most_change_state = seasonal_avg_pm25["Percentage Change"].abs().idxmax()
most_change_value = seasonal_avg_pm25.loc[most_change_state, "Percentage Change"]

print("Percentage Change in PM2.5 Levels (Monsoon vs Summer) for each state:")
print(seasonal_avg_pm25[["Percentage Change"]])
print(f"\nThe state with the highest absolute change in PM2.5 is {most_change_state} with a {most_change_value:.2f}% change.")

df_delhi = df[df["state"] == "Delhi"]

def classify_season(month):
    if month in [12, 1, 2]: 
        return "Winter"
    elif month in [3, 4, 5]:  
        return "Summer"
    elif month in [6, 7, 8, 9]: 
        return "Monsoon"

df_delhi["Season"] = df_delhi["Timestamp"].dt.month.map(classify_season)

seasonal_avg_pm25 = df_delhi.groupby([df_delhi["Timestamp"].dt.year, "Season"])["PM2.5"].mean().unstack()

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
for season in ["Winter", "Summer", "Monsoon"]:
    plt.plot(seasonal_avg_pm25.index, seasonal_avg_pm25[season], marker="o", linestyle="-", label=season)
plt.legend(title = "Season")

print("Winter has the most pollution because cold air traps it, monsoon has the least as rain cleans the air, and summer has moderate pollution from dust and factories.")

Winter has the most pollution because cold air traps it, monsoon has the least as rain cleans the air, and summer has moderate pollution from dust and factories.

df["Timestamp"] = pd.to_datetime(df["Timestamp"])
pollution_2021 = df[df["Timestamp"].dt.year == 2021]

state_pm25_avg = pollution_2021.groupby("state")["PM2.5"].mean().reset_index()

state_funding = df_2.groupby("state")["Total fund released"].sum().reset_index()

state_pm25_avg = state_pm25_avg.merge(state_funding, on="state", how="left")

state_pm25_avg["NCAP Funded"] = state_pm25_avg["Total fund released"].fillna(0) > 0

avg_pm25_funded = state_pm25_avg[state_pm25_avg["NCAP Funded"]]["PM2.5"].mean()
avg_pm25_non_funded = state_pm25_avg[~state_pm25_avg["NCAP Funded"]]["PM2.5"].mean()

print(f"Average PM2.5 in NCAP-funded states: {avg_pm25_funded:.2f}")
print(f"Average PM2.5 in non-funded states: {avg_pm25_non_funded:.2f}")

plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))
plt.bar(["NCAP Funded", "Non-Funded"], [avg_pm25_funded, avg_pm25_non_funded], color=["green", "red"])
plt.show()

Average PM2.5 in NCAP-funded states: 48.94
Average PM2.5 in non-funded states: 32.95

df["Timestamp"] = pd.to_datetime(df["Timestamp"])

for col in ["Amount released during FY 2019-20", "Amount released during FY 2020-21", "Amount released during FY 2021-22", "Total fund released"]:
    df_2[col] = pd.to_numeric(df_2[col], errors="coerce")

assam_pm25 = df[df["state"] == "Assam"].copy()
assam_pm25["Year"] = assam_pm25["Timestamp"].dt.year 
pm25_trend = assam_pm25.groupby("Year")["PM2.5"].mean().reset_index()

assam_funding = df_2[df_2["state"] == "Assam"]

funding_by_year = pd.DataFrame({
    "Year": [2019, 2020, 2021],  
    "Total fund released": [
        assam_funding["Amount released during FY 2019-20"].sum(),
        assam_funding["Amount released during FY 2020-21"].sum(),
        assam_funding["Amount released during FY 2021-22"].sum()
    ]
})

assam_trend = pm25_trend.merge(funding_by_year, on="Year", how="left")
assam_trend = assam_trend[assam_trend["Year"].isin([2019, 2020, 2021])]


fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))

ax1.set_xlabel("Year")
ax1.set_ylabel("Average PM2.5 Level", color="red")
ax1.plot(assam_trend["Year"], assam_trend["PM2.5"], marker="o", color="red", label="PM2.5 Level")
ax1.tick_params(axis="y", labelcolor="red")

ax2 = ax1.twinx()
ax2.set_ylabel("NCAP Funding (Crores)", color="blue")
ax2.bar(assam_trend["Year"], assam_trend["Total fund released"], alpha=0.5, color="blue", label="NCAP Funding")
ax2.tick_params(axis="y", labelcolor="blue")

plt.title("PM2.5 Levels vs. NCAP Funding in Assam (Time Series)")
fig.tight_layout()
plt.show()

df["Timestamp"] = pd.to_datetime(df["Timestamp"])

delhi_data = df[df["city"] == "Delhi"]

delhi_data["Year"] = delhi_data["Timestamp"].dt.year
delhi_data["Month"] = delhi_data["Timestamp"].dt.month

diwali_months = [10, 11] 
new_year_month = [1]  

monthly_avg_pm25 = delhi_data.groupby(["Year", "Month"])["PM2.5"].mean().reset_index()

pivot_pm25 = monthly_avg_pm25.pivot(index="Month", columns="Year", values="PM2.5")

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
for year in [2018, 2019, 2020]:
    plt.plot(pivot_pm25.index, pivot_pm25[year], marker="o", label=f"{year}")

for year in [2018, 2019, 2020]:
    diwali_avg = pivot_pm25.loc[diwali_months, year].mean()  
    new_year_avg = pivot_pm25.loc[new_year_month, year].mean()  
    
    max_diwali_pm25 = pivot_pm25.loc[diwali_months, year].max()
    max_new_year_pm25 = pivot_pm25.loc[new_year_month, year].max()
    
    max_diwali_month = pivot_pm25.loc[diwali_months, year].idxmax()
    max_new_year_month = pivot_pm25.loc[new_year_month, year].idxmax()
    
    plt.annotate(f"Diwali {year}", xy=(max_diwali_month, max_diwali_pm25),
                 xytext=(max_diwali_month, max_diwali_pm25 + 20),
                 arrowprops=dict(facecolor="red", arrowstyle="->"), fontsize=10, color="red")
    
    plt.annotate(f"New Year {year}", xy=(max_new_year_month, max_new_year_pm25),
                 xytext=(max_new_year_month, max_new_year_pm25 + 20),
                 arrowprops=dict(facecolor="blue", arrowstyle="->"), fontsize=10, color="blue")

plt.xlabel("Month")
plt.ylabel("Average PM2.5 (g/m^3)")
plt.title("PM2.5 Levels in Delhi (2018-2020) During Festivals vs. Regular Months")
plt.xticks(np.arange(1, 13), ["Jan", "Feb", "Mar", "Apr", "May", "Jun", "Jul", "Aug", "Sep", "Oct", "Nov", "Dec"])
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

#  Identifying Cities with High Funding but Low Utilization Funds

df_2["Total fund released"] = pd.to_numeric(df_2["Total fund released"], errors="coerce")
df_2["Utilisation as on June 2022"] = pd.to_numeric(df_2["Utilisation as on June 2022"], errors="coerce")

df_2["Utilization Percentage"] = (df_2["Utilisation as on June 2022"] / df_2["Total fund released"]) * 100

high_funding_threshold = df_2["Total fund released"].quantile(0.75) 
low_utilization_threshold = 50  

low_utilization_cities = df_2[
    (df_2["Total fund released"] >= high_funding_threshold) & 
    (df_2["Utilization Percentage"] < low_utilization_threshold)
]

low_utilization_cities = low_utilization_cities.sort_values(by="Total fund released", ascending=False)

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
plt.barh(low_utilization_cities["City"], low_utilization_cities["Utilization Percentage"], color='red')
plt.xlabel("Utilization Percentage")
plt.ylabel("City")
plt.title("Cities with High NCAP Funding but Low Utilization")
plt.gca().invert_yaxis() 
plt.grid(axis='x', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)
plt.show()

print(low_utilization_cities[["state", "City", "Total fund released", "Utilization Percentage"]])
